<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This ThinBackend writes individual module indexes to files, instead of</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><Highlight kind="comment">/// To find the path to write the index to, the backend checks if the path has a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><Highlight kind="comment">/// prefix of OldPrefix; if so, it replaces that prefix with NewPrefix. It then</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><Highlight kind="comment">/// appends &quot;.thinlto.bc&quot; and writes the index to that path. If</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ShouldEmitImportsFiles is true it also writes a list of imported files to a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><Highlight kind="comment">/// similar path with &quot;.imports&quot; appended instead.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><Highlight kind="comment">/// LinkedObjectsFile is an output stream to write the list of object files for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the final ThinLTO linking. Can be nullptr.  If LinkedObjectsFile is not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00308" /><CodeLine lineNumber="308"><Highlight kind="comment">/// nullptr and NativeObjectPrefix is not empty then it replaces the prefix of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00309" /><CodeLine lineNumber="309"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the objects with NativeObjectPrefix instead of NewPrefix. OnWrite is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><Highlight kind="comment">/// callback which receives module identifier and notifies LTO user that index</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><Highlight kind="comment">/// file for the module (and optionally imports file) was created.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class implements a resolution-based interface to LLVM&#39;s LTO</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="comment">/// functionality. It supports regular LTO, parallel LTO code generation and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ThinLTO. You can use it from a linker in the following way:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - Set hooks and code generation options (see lto::Config struct defined in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><Highlight kind="comment">///   Config.h), and use the lto::Config object to create an lto::LTO object.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - Create lto::InputFile objects using lto::InputFile::create(), then use</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><Highlight kind="comment">///   the symbols() function to enumerate its symbols and compute a resolution</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00327" /><CodeLine lineNumber="327"><Highlight kind="comment">///   for each symbol (see SymbolResolution below).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00328" /><CodeLine lineNumber="328"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - After the linker has visited each input file (and each regular object</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00329" /><CodeLine lineNumber="329"><Highlight kind="comment">///   file) and computed a resolution for each symbol, take each lto::InputFile</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00330" /><CodeLine lineNumber="330"><Highlight kind="comment">///   and pass it and an array of symbol resolutions to the add() function.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - Call the getMaxTasks() function to get an upper bound on the number of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><Highlight kind="comment">///   native object files that LTO may add to the link.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - Call the run() function. This function will use the supplied AddStream</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><Highlight kind="comment">///   and Cache functions to add up to getMaxTasks() native object files to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><Highlight kind="comment">///   the link.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
